projects.title: Wonderware SCADA DAserver wrapper for .NET class
projects.description:
Please read & understand in full before applying. Submit any questions with your response. The budget is just a placeholder, you bid your best quote & delivery time. 
Wonderware Archestra is a SCADA system using DAserver for communications with outside systems. Need you to create a wrapper app in MS Vis Std for a .NET standard class which will emulate as a DA server to Wonderware 2014 R2 &  later versions (legacy system, not system platform). You may have to use DAS toolkit or like it to test/create the wrapper with. The .NET std class will at lease perform a TCP & UDP socket connect/disconnect with an external system, send/receive some arbitrary ascii text data. The external system could be a simple test app built with this class also. You may build this class yourself or we can supply one, on your request. This functionality will eventually be executed via Wonderware client test app via DAserver wrapper & then via the .NET std class. DAserver running on same PC as client. The external app is what your Wonderware client test app, the DAserver app/wrapper/.NET class system will connect & communicate with.
An example product that does this process(we did not build it, so do not know how internally this was done) is
https://en.freedownloadmanager.org/Windows-PC/Wonderware-SIDirect-DAServer-FREE.html

PLEASE APPLY ONLY IF YOU ARE SERIOUS, CAPABLE & EXPERIENCED WITH & HAVE DAS TOOLKIT.
All the source developed & anything else (except MS products) needed to fully maintain it in future will need to be delivered. If milestone payments desired, then submit details with response. No upfront given & source will be required from you, evaluated before any payment released. Submit a plan of action for the project also. Thank you for your help, time & interest.

    1. Previous candle monthly = MH and ML for previous month and 2 month before (Red color and label to differentiate) 
    2. Previous Candle weekly = WH and WL for previous month and 2 week before (Blue color and label to differentiate)
    3. Previous Candle Daily = DH and DL daily update (Purple color different than weekly and monthly)
-How to measure bullish Candle or bearish of weekly candle as below (New)
    1. Highest candle - close candle > Close candle - lowest candle = Bearish weekly candle (focus on selling)
    2. Close candle - lowest candle > highest candle - close candle = Bullish candle (focus on buying)
    3. Highest candle - close candle = Closed candle - lowest candle = Doji candle (20 PID below closed candle - open candle) (Disable entry)

projects.title: parental control - turning on and off internet
projects.description:
I need to create on a Mikrotik router the following:

A simple way for parents to turn on and off the internet remotely on selected mikrotik router ports

We need 2 kind of setups:
WAN with static IP 
WAN with dhcp IP


In both cases user (parent) will know the External IP (isp) of the router.
User must be able to do the following:
1.	Turn on and off the internet on selected ports
2.	Create a weekly or daily schedule on selected ports for internet to be on or off.

Access on router from user can be done through a web based (or not) application. We are open to any solution doing the above.
